Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (Amazon EC2) is a web service that provides secure, resizable compute capacity in the cloud.

A workload is memory-intensive when it stores or holds large amounts of data in RAM.
A workload is compute-intensive when it spends most of its time performing CPU-heavy calculations.

pem key permission:
While doing ssh to ec2 you must first give 600 permission to pem file then do ssh
ssh -i file-name.pem ubuntu@ip

Access ec2:
if you deployed any service on ec2 and try to access on (http) browser by default it will not be accessible so you must add inbound rule.
instance-id ---> security ---> security-group-link ---> inbound rules
